  "base_commit": "e64908eb62c52a1a36dde006f6837baf619c5c1e",
  "pr_number": 3595,
  "issue_number": 3593,
  "issue_title": "AI: add a Reanimator / graveyard-recursion deck-feature axis + policy",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n`phase-ai` has no concept of the **reanimator** archetype: reanimation spells that put a big creature from a graveyard onto the battlefield, the **enablers** that fill the graveyard (self-mill, discard), and the high-impact **payoffs** (expensive creatures) reanimated ahead of curve. The AI values none of this as a *plan* \u2014 it won't prioritize self-milling/discarding to set up a reanimation, nor value holding a reanimation spell for a fat target. This adds the missing `ReanimatorFeature` + payoff-gated policy via the supported `add-ai-feature-policy` pattern.\n\n## Why it's valuable / necessary\nReanimator is a recurring archetype across Modern (Goryo's Vengeance, Persist), Legacy (Reanimate, Animate Dead, Exhume, Entomb), Pioneer (Greasefang), and Commander (Unburial Rites, Reanimate). The engine already resolves these cards correctly (verified: Reanimate, Unburial Rites, Exhume, Goryo's Vengeance all parse to the expected typed AST), but the AI plays them as disconnected goodstuff \u2014 no axis ties \"fill graveyard \u2192 reanimate threat.\"\n\n**Support, measured directly in `card-data.json` (34,771 cards):**\n- **~683 cards** carry a graveyard\u2192battlefield `Effect::ChangeZone` (`origin = Graveyard`, `destination = Battlefield`) \u2014 the reanimation-**payoff** signature.\n- **~303 of those** target a creature `TargetFilter` \u2014 the core payoff class the detector keys on.\n- Enablers are broad: **~570 cards** with a `Mill` effect, **~1,942** with a `Discard` effect.\n\n> An earlier draft cited \"3,958 cards with a graveyard\u2192battlefield signature.\" That number was a loose union of all graveyard-adjacent effects and is corrected above: the GY\u2192BF payoff class is ~300\u2013700 cards. Still comfortably axis-worthy \u2014 larger than several existing niche axes \u2014 but the support claim is now honest.\n\n## Current behavior\n`DeckFeatures::analyze` (`features/mod.rs`) detects 12 structural axes; none recognizes reanimation. Existing graveyard-adjacent AI logic is **targeting-side only**:\n- `policies/recursion_awareness.rs` \u2014 avoids feeding an opponent's recursive / death-trigger creature to a harmful effect (a targeting heuristic).\n- `policies/mill_targeting.rs` \u2014 optimizes *who* to mill; notably carries `SELF_MILL_PENALTY = -0.2`, i.e. it **discourages** self-mill when not obviously beneficial.\n\nNeither encodes a deck-level \"enabler \u2192 reanimation payoff\" plan. **Integration note:** the new policy's enabler bonus (raising the value of self-mill) sums against `mill_targeting`'s self-mill penalty in the registry, so it must be calibrated to overcome that penalty only when reanimation payoffs **and** worthwhile targets are both present.\n\n## Correct behavior\nA `ReanimatorFeature` detects three structural roles over the typed AST (parts-based, no card-name matching):\n- **Reanimation payoffs** \u2014 `Effect::ChangeZone` (`crates/engine/src/types/ability.rs:7147`) with `origin = Some(Graveyard)`, `destination = Battlefield`, and a creature `TargetFilter` (mirrors how `features/landfall.rs` keys off `TriggerMode::ChangesZone` + `Zone::Battlefield`).\n- **Enablers** \u2014 self-mill (`Effect::Mill` targeting the controller) and discard-as-resource (`Effect::Discard` of own cards), which load the graveyard.\n- **Targets/fuel** \u2014 high-mana-value creatures (the threats worth reanimating).\n\nA companion **payoff-gated** `TacticalPolicy` raises the value of enabler plays (self-mill/discard) and of deploying/holding reanimation **only** when the deck contains both reanimation payoffs and worthwhile targets, and stays inert otherwise.\n\n## Design \u2014 follow the thin payoff precedent (lifegain / enchantments)\nBuild at the scale the logic genuinely needs, matching the **freshly-blessed** thin feature-+-payoff pattern, not a padded one:\n- `features/lifegain.rs` (183 ln) + `policies/lifegain_payoff.rs` + `PolicyId::LifegainPayoff`\n- `features/enchantments.rs` (199 ln) + `policies/enchantments_payoff.rs` + `PolicyId::EnchantmentsPayoff`\n\nThree structural roles over `ChangeZone` / `Mill` / `Discard` + an MV threshold is a thin-feature shape \u2014 size the detector like `lifegain`/`enchantments`, **not** `aristocrats.rs` (1002 ln). Do not inflate node count to chase a scoring metric; per CLAUDE.md every abstraction must earn its keep.\n\n1. **New `crates/phase-ai/src/features/reanimator.rs`** \u2014 `pub struct ReanimatorFeature { reanimation_count, enabler_count, target_count, commitment }` + structural `detect()`. Payoff-weighted commitment (mirror the lifegain calibration so incidental graveyard interaction stays inert).\n2. **`features/mod.rs`** \u2014 `pub mod reanimator;`, re-export, `DeckFeatures` field, `analyze()` wiring.\n3. **New `crates/phase-ai/src/policies/reanimator_payoff.rs`** \u2014 payoff-gated `TacticalPolicy`, band-helper scored, delta through a new UNTUNED `PolicyPenalties` knob.\n4. **`policies/registry.rs`** \u2014 `PolicyId::ReanimatorPayoff` + default registration.\n5. **Single authority** \u2014 `pub(crate) fn is_reanimation_payoff(...)` / `is_graveyard_enabler(...)` shared by detector and policy.\n6. **Duel suite / gate coverage** \u2014 add `FeatureKind::Reanimator` (and to `FeatureKind::ALL`), plus a reanimator matchup that the required gate exercises. `pioneer/orzhov-greasefang.json` already exists (Greasefang reanimates a vehicle) as a partial anchor; prefer a dedicated reanimator deck (Legacy/Modern Reanimate or Exhume shell) verified to clear `COMMITMENT_FLOOR`. A new axis without a floor-crossing gate matchup ships dormant.\n7. **Tests in SEPARATE files** \u2014 impl files contain **no** `#[cfg(test)]`; declare the test submodule from the parent `mod.rs` (`#[cfg(test)] mod reanimator_tests;`), never from the impl file.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `ReanimatorFeature` detects reanimation payoffs / enablers / targets (parts-based, not name-matching) and is wired into `DeckFeatures::analyze`.\n- [ ] A payoff-gated `reanimator_payoff` `TacticalPolicy` registered in `PolicyRegistry::default`, calibrated to overcome `mill_targeting`'s self-mill penalty only when payoffs + targets are both present.\n- [ ] `FeatureKind::Reanimator` added; a reanimator matchup is in the **required** gate's `DEFAULT_QUICK_FILTER`, with a `#[ignore]` test asserting the deck clears `COMMITMENT_FLOOR`, and the regenerated baseline shows it as a real PASS row (policy active).\n- [ ] Detector + policy tests in separate files (impl files inline-test-free); calibration anchors included.\n- [ ] No `no_name_matching` / `score_contract` lint violation; `PolicyPenalties` field-coverage test passes (knob registered UNTUNED).\n\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-17T14:09:48.000Z",
